the state of california, the csu and san jose state university operate on a fiscal year calendar, which officially begins july 1and ends june 30. finance strives to have an efficient and timely closing of the university's books at june 30 and provide accurate financial reporting to the state controllers office and chancellors office.it is important for campus departments to review and reconcile their accounts throughout the fiscal year. active participation by departments towards their finances allows for a true snapshot of their financial health.in preparation for year-end, departments should take note of the procedures and process timelines provided in our fiscal year-end guide for making corrections, purchase and payment requests, and deposits.fiscal year-end 21/22 campus deadlines phone: 408-924-1558 email: financeconnect@sjsu.edu finance and business services san jose state university 60 south market street suite 470 san jose, ca 95113